        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 9:16AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 916 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of showers and
isolated thunderstorms extending from over Oil City to near Minden,
or extending from 20 miles northwest of Shreveport to near Minden,
moving north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Minden, Springhill, Homer, Vivian, Haynesville, Benton, Sibley,
Cullen, Plain Dealing, Cotton Valley, Oil City, Sarepta,
Mooringsport, Bradley, Taylor, Emerson, Hosston, Dixie Inn,
Dubberly and Rodessa.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
